Town Boards
Planning Commission
Judi Costanzo – Chairperson
Gail Guinta
Tonya Whitehurst
Mike Rodgers
Raymond Baxter
Randy Donaldson
The Planning Commission meets the third (3rd) Tuesday of the month at 7:00 P.M., on an as needed basis to consider rezoning and comprehensive plan amendment requests. The Planning Commission is an advisory Board and makes recommendations to the Town Council for a final decision.
Zoning Board of Adjustment
Jasmine Rivera
Leo Granger
Stacy Suarez
Annarose Larsen
The Zoning Board of Adjustment meets the third (3rd) Monday of the month at 7:30 P.M., on an as needed basis to consider Special Exceptions, Variances and Yard Modification requests. Their decisions are final, but appeals can be made to the Town Council.
Tree Board
Timothy Keyser
Grace Chlastawa
Evelyn Waters DuPont
Laverne Larsen
The purpose of this Ordinance is to declare and define the Town’s power and authority over all trees, plants and shrubs located within the street rights-of-ways, parks and other places owned or legally controlled by the Town of Interlachen, Florida. Such power and authority shall promote and protect the public health, safety and general welfare and further, shall accentuate the scenic, cultural, historical and aesthetic attributes of the Town of Interlachen by establishing procedures and practices for fulfilling these purposes.
Click Here to Download Ordinance 02-7

Economic Development Task Force
Vacancy
The Economic Development Task Force meets if the Town considers applying for an Economic Development Block Grant. The Task Force considers the options for the grant application and makes a recommendation to the Town Council.
Citizens Advisory Task Force (CATF) For CDBG Projects
Erika Judson
Shelton Griffis
The Citizens Advisory Task Force meets if the Town considers applying for an Community Development Block Grant. The Task Force considers the options for the grant application and makes a recommendation to the Town Council.
Better Place Plan Committee
Tony Minotti
Thomas Campbell
Jason Matchett
The Better Place Plan Oversite Committee brings ideas before the Council on ways to spend Better Place Plan monies for Town improvements.

Joni Conner – Chairperson
Elizabeth Hanes
Anna Rose Larsen
Mike Rodgers
Judi Costanzo
